'The Damned': Felix Nussbaum's bleak depiction of life in Nazi Germany was
completed in 1944; months later he was on board the last deportation train
to succeed in leaving occupied Brussels ahead of the approaching Allies to
his death at Auschwitz. Taken from Sergiusz's Michalski's 'New Objectivity'
(Taschen, 220 pages)
