<HEADLINE>
FT  06 AUG 94 / Finance and the Family: Annuity rates
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The table (right) shows the latest compulsory purchase annuity rates for
those with Pounds 100,000 to invest. Since the payout can vary greatly
between life offices, it is important for those buying an annuity to shop
around for the most suitable and the best rate.
'The annuities market has slowed from the rapid increases it experienced
during the first half of the year especially after gilt rates, upon which
annuity rates are dependent, dropped by half a percent over the last month,'
said Peter Quinton of the Annuity Bureau.
'A number of providers have lowered their rates since the last annuity
table, with Royal Life dropping by 2 per cent and the Prudential by 1.9 per
cent. Companies which have increased their annuity rates include Britannic
Assurance, Axa Equity &amp; Law, Equitable Life and Norwich Union.'
William Burrows, of Annuity Direct, said: 'After a stable period for annuity
rates in June, rates increased slightly in the middle of July. Since January
annuity rates have increased by over 14 per cent, a direct response to the
increase in gilt yields.
'The future trend for annuity rates will be influenced by expectations for
inflation and interest rates.
'The indicators suggest that annuity rates will continue to increase, albeit
slowly. However, I do not expect rates to rise significantly during the rest
of summer even if interest rates are increased.'
