FT  06 AUG 94 / Finance and the Family: More smaller companies cheer - At a
glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
It has been another good week for UK smaller companies. The Hoare Govett
Smaller Companies Index (capital gains version) climbed 1.3 per cent to
1,673.74 over the week to August 4. The index is down by 0.8 per cent since
the start of the year but compares relatively well to the FT-SE-A All-share
index, which is down by 4 per cent.
