<TEXT>
Bullough, the diversified engineering and office products group, yesterday
said it was expanding its core heating business with the Pounds 9.89m
acquisition of Trianco Group, the privately-owned boiler manufacturer.
It is the first acquisition since Mr Gordon Bond took over as chief
executive in January and refocused the company on four key areas:
refrigeration, engineering, office products and heating.
'Trianco fits in with our strategy of building competitive advantage and
market share in our core business-es.'
Bullough is issuing Pounds 9.74m of six year loan notes and paying Pounds
150,000 cash for the Sheffield-based company. Mr Bond said the group also
planned to redeem Pounds 1.9m of Trianco cumulative preference shares and
would assume its Pounds 2.2m net borrowings.
Trianco, which manufactures and sells oil and gas boilers, reported pre-tax
losses of Pounds 1.08m after exceptional provisions of Pounds 1.8m for the
year to December 31. At the operating level, profits were Pounds 778,000 on
turnover of Pounds 12.6m.
Bullough's heating division made operating profits of Pounds 4.1m on sales
of Pounds 35.1m in the 12 months to October 31.
