   QUITO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Ecuadorian government announced the sale of a 75 per cent share in the
state airline, Ecuatoriana, following nearly a year of indecision that left
the financially troubled airline grounded. The government has now pledged to
assume the airline's debt portfolio, which exceeds Dollars 100m. The
transformation into a stock company will take place in weeks. Ecuatoriana's
routes to destinations throughout North and South America may attract
investors. The only remaining company-owned aircraft was confiscated by
creditors nearly eight months ago and since then has been stranded in
Panama. Nearly all the airline's staff had been sacked, leaving only some 50
employees.
