FT  05 AUG 94 / International Company News: BPA rejects BCP stake offer
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The executive board of Banco Portugues do Atlantico, Portugal's second
largest bank, has formally rejected a public offer by Banco Comercial
Portugues, a smaller competitor, for a controlling stake of BPA.
In a letter to Portugal's stock exchange commission (CMVM), the board said
the bid was not in the best interests of BPA shareholders. BCP is offering
Es132bn for 40 per cent of BPA.
