FT  05 AUG 94 / International Capital Markets: Mexican shares given greater
SEAQ display
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NORMA COHEN, Investments Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mexican equities will be quoted on the London Stock Exchange's SEAQ
International screen under their own country heading from August 15, the
Stock Exchange said yesterday.
The exchange said the move 'recognises the maturing of the Mexican market'.
Mexican shares are already listed on SEAQ International, the Exchange's
bulletin board for dealing prices in non-UK shares, but only under a broader
Developing Markets Sector.
The total volume of SEAQ International in firm-quoted Mexican stocks last
year was Pounds 3.6bn, or 4 per cent of volume on the Mexican Stock
Exchange.
