first half of the current year. It has also bought about 500 plots in Co
Wicklow, and since the year end had acquired an investment property in
Dublin for IPounds 3.5m with an initial yield of 9.1 per cent.
Earnings per share were 14.52p (4.06p), and a final dividend of 3p brings
the total for the year to 5p (2p).
